{"lemma":"مُعْضِلَةٌ","slug":"مُعْضِلَةٌ","root":"ع.ض.ل","root_slug":"ع-ض-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ض-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29478"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%B6%D9%90%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"problem, riddle, enigma, dilemma"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/muʕ.dˤi.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29478","headword_ar":"مُعْضِلَةٌ","root":"EDl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as a subst.] sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEoDilaAtN","text_ar":"مُعْضِلَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distressing, events:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mEDlp","text_ar":"معضلة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. accord. to the context ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaD~ilapN","text_ar":"مُعَضِّلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficult,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strait, calamity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 258.) Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaD~ilapN","text_ar":"مُعَضِّلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a case, that is strait in respect of the ways of getting out therefrom."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEuw*u biA@ll~`hi mino kul~i muEoDilapK layosa lahaA A^abuw HasanK","text_ar":"اَعُوذُ بِا@للّٰهِ مِنْ كُلِّ مُعْضِلَةٍ لَيْسَ لَهَا اَبُو حَسَنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) or, as some relate it, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaD~ilapK","text_ar":"مُعَضِّلَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) is a saying of 'Omar, (so in the O, but in the TA “ in the trad. of Ibn-'Omar, ”) who meant thereby ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I seek protection by God from"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every difficult question"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for which there is no Aboo- Hasan;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, no one such as 'Alee the son of Aboo-Tálib, who was surnamed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw AlHasani","text_ar":"اَبُو الحَسَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and was celebrated for his answers to what are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmasaAy^ilu AlmuEoDilaAt","text_ar":"المَسَايِلُ المُعْضِلَات"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is related by En-Nawawee, in his Biographical Dictionary (p. 437)]: (O, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abw Hsn","text_ar":"ابو حسن"},{"kind":"text","text":", though determinate, is put in the place of that which is indeterminate. (IAth, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","O","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}